creator: Islam.ms
descriptionHtml:
This Accurate Prayer Time and Qiblah App has the following features:

- Islamic Prayer Times and Qibla Compass finder and Locator for cities worldwide

- Ramadan 2022 timetable.
- Imsak: abstinence Schedule for fasters.

- Hegira date, Islamic date based on visual observation
- Save hegira date on the calendar
- Write in the Calendar an event such as birth, menstruation ... with Hegira date

- Qiblah finder on Google Maps.

- The compass number with the calculation of the magnetic deviation for Qiblah.

- Possibility of moving the marker on the map and having the direction of the Qiblah as well as the number of the compass

Detecting the position. Geolocation for Salat Times and Qiblah

Widget for Prayer Times

Adhan for Prayers and for ṣubḥ Fajr

Protection Invocations and Evocations

Subḥah Counter

Zakat Calculation

Alarm for Qiyam before fajr

Times for Fasting and Sahoor Ramadan 2023

voice search: dictate a place to get calculation of Prayer times & Qibla

Ability to enter latitude and longitude directly into the search field
Example: 48.86 2.35 (a space between latitude and longitude)

Islamic Inheritance Calculation App

Search prayer times and qibla without internet with GPS

Calculate the parts of the night

Learn Islam and the science of religion

Receive regular Islamic information in the application in Arabic, French, English, Spanish

Numerous visual observations were made to adopt a reliable method of calculation.

Allâh ta`âlâ said : { إِنَّ الصَّلاَةَ كَانَتْ عَلَى الْمُؤْمِنِينَ كِتَابًا مَّوْقُوتًا } [sôurat An-Niçâ’] which means: « Certainly the prayer was prescribed for believers in his time ». It is a duty to check the times of prayers by observation and it is not enough to rely on a schedule based on the simple calculation. See https://www.islam.ms/en/islamic-prayer-times
